2nd Street, west side, north of 26th Avenue, on the East River, showing the Astoria Light and what Mr. Sperr calls the Board of Education Building. Here was located Fort Stevens and United States Government Works. In 1873 the Eagle Oil Works occupied the site.

P. L. Sperr
View 1: June, 1927
Views 2,3: March, 1931
